	 <h2>News</h2>
	  <br>
        Hong Lu, Jun Yang, Zhigang Liu, Nicholas D. Lane, Tanzeem Choudhury, Andrew T. Campbell, The Jigsaw Continuous Sensing Engine for Mobile Phone Applications. To appear in 8th ACM Conference on Embedded Networked Sensor Systems (SenSys 2010), Zurich, Switzerland November 3-5, 2010.
	 <br>
	 <br>
         <h2>About me</h2>
	  <br>
	I am a fifth year Ph.D. student in the <a href="http://www.cs.dartmouth.edu/" target="_blank">Department of Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://www.dartmouth.edu/" target="_blank">Dartmouth College</a>,  working with <a href="http://www.cs.dartmouth.edu/%7Ecampbell">Andrew T. Campbell</a>. I am currently part of: the <a href="http://sensorlab.cs.dartmouth.edu/">Mobile Sensing Group</a>,the <a href="http://metrosense.cs.dartmouth.edu/">MetroSense project</a>  and <a href="http://cenceme.org/">CenceMe</a>. I got my bachelor and master degrees from the department of Computer Science, <a href="http://www.tju.edu.cn/english/">Tianjin University</a>, Tianjin, China.
         <br>
	 <br>
				
	<h2>My Research Interests</h2>
	  <br>
	   Area: pervasive computing, mobile sensing system, human behavior modeling, and machine learning
	  <br><br>
My current research focuses on developing  people-centric sensing system and inference techniques for mobile phones, which allow us to monitor, understand, and even predict people’s physical and social activities in their everyday life. My primarily interest is developing scalable sensing system for modeling and analyzing human behavior. I built prototype mobile applications based on a variety of mobile platforms (e.g., apple iPhone, Nokia N95/N900, Google Android). I have experience on a handful of domains of mobile sensing systems including: system architecture (SoundSense, Jigsaw), applications(CenceMe), power management, and multi-modality activity recognition (i.e., audio, location, accelerometer, gyro). My research papers appeared in a number of top conferences including ACM MobiSys, Pervasive, ACM Sensys, AAAI, and so on.
